posts.title: MOST of the grants awarded by USAID are scams. Here's PROOF
posts.content:
I just randomly picked a few to look at from 2024: https://www.usaspending.gov/search/?hash=02e72c86eb0eec87ac6ef0752206324c

Here's a few random ones; but almost EVERY single one (outside of the big names like Deloitte) I'm pretty sure are scams:

  1. GLOBAL SOLUTIONS VENTURES, LLC got $29.5 Million in 2024. Address is 3 BETHESDA METRO CTR STE 700 BETHESDA, MD. Guess what? It's a fucking EasyOffice coworking space which rents for $279/month. It's not even a real office. Hardly the sort of entity that should get $29.5M a year. https://www.usaspending.gov/recipient/59c5ce32-7e9a-fdb6-11d1-1f6cbeab48e6-C/latest

https://www.easyoffices.com/us/available-office-space/md/bethesda/3-bethesda-metro-center

  1. Zemitek, LLC got $33 Million. Guess what's the address? The same one as the above, even the same Suite number in the coworking space. https://www.usaspending.gov/recipient/4c6235f2-c686-8581-2e85-d157143831a0-C/latest

  2. Eagle One Solutions, Inc. got $9.8 Million. A closer inspection shows it's one out of many shell companies owned by Chenega Professional Services, which itself is part of the Chenega Corporation of Alaska. I spent 15 minutes on their website(s) and STILL have no idea what they do beyond generic "support services". The websites are all stock photos, with no real people, employees, or real names. Take a look for yourself: https://chenegaps.com/about-us/

https://www.usaspending.gov/recipient/371ac184-2a44-0ced-d710-e8570389cfed-C/latest

Note how the grants started and ended ONLY during Biden's term. Google Maps of the address shows the whole building belongs to the BECO construction company, with not a single sign saying anything about the shell company.

  1. Socha, LLC, got $35.8 Million. Their address: 2420 21st St, Columbus NE. It's a literally just somebody's house (and a small one at that). Take a look at one specific contract here: https://www.usaspending.gov/award/CONT_AWD_72061522M00004_7200_47QRAA19D005J_4732

They got $30 million for "USAID LOCALIZATION, INCLUSION, AND SUSTAINABILITY ACTIVITY (LISA) THE PURPOSE OF THE USAID INCLUSION AND LOCALIZATION MECHANISM IS TO SUPPORT USAID/KENYA AND EAST AFRICA (KEA) STAFF AND STAKEHOLDERS TO BE MORE EFFICIENT, EFFECTIVE, TRANSPARENT" Their website: https://socha.net

The landing page has a bunch of BS about 'process and impact evaluations'. Looking at the 'Current Projects' - it's just some vague nonsense about doing 'monitoring and evaluations' in Africa. $30M? Really?

  1. Too many to list but there are a ton of "tech consulting" LLCs that all follow the same pattern; a BS website with stock photos and hand-wavy nonsense about building software for a federal contract. Here's one example: https://highlighttech.com/case-study-transformative-enterprise-technology-solutions/

What they describe doesn't sound like it was written by someone who knows what they're talking about - its just buzzwords. Even IF we assume what they say is true, they're just selling COTS consumer software to some govt agency. At the very LEAST, DOGE can look into why there are so many redundant contracts to these companies, because we're paying thousands of these "consultants" to sell the same thing! ("Hey <agency>, just migrate to AWS!" except it happens thousands of times over and over again instead of the govt sharing that knowledge internally)

You can see for yourself, just use the link up top. Start at page 7 or so, when the grants are under $15M and its alot easier to see the bullshit-sounding company names. This shit was hiding in plain sight, for years.

The sheer amount of bullshit grants being awarded means this is absolutely deliberate. I clearly see what Elon meant when he said the WHOLE THING is a ball of worms. I got so angry after looking at this because every single one of those I clicked were almost certainly scams or shell companies getting awarded our money. And MOST happened in the last few years.
